@NODE Startup
@TITLE "misterbanana  Startup"


    @{b}Startup@{ub}

    
    You can start MisterBanana from Ambient or from the
    CLI.
 

    @{b}Ambient@{ub}

    MisterBanana supports all default MUI- and Commodity-
    tooltypes.


    @{b}CLI@{ub}

    It has no options. Just start it.

@ENDNODE


@NODE MainWindow
@TITLE "misterbanana  Main window"


    @{b}Main window@{ub}


    Banana! Banana!

    Well, right click directly on the banana opens the hotlist, outside (but still
    with activated window) lets you play around in the normal menu (just in case
    you wondered).

    While Mr.Banana is activated you can enter a secret code to activate world
    destruction. Have fun!

@ENDNODE

@NODE MenuOptions
@TITLE "misterbanana  Menuoptions"


    @{b}Menu options@{ub}


    @{b}Project@{ub}

        About...

            Opens the About window with copyright information and
            credits.

        About MUI...

            Opens MUIs About window.

        Quit

            Quits MisterBanana immediatelly.


    @{b}Settings:@{ub}

        Use Anonymizer
            Uses an anonymizer for selected URLs from the hotlist.

        Transparency
            Activates faked transparency when possible.

        Snapshot
        Unsnapshot

            Snapshots or unsnapshots MisterBananas window.

        MUI...

            Opens MUI Settings. Here you can define the look
            of MisterBanana.

            To change the look, just go to "Buttons" and change
            Background and Frame for normal Gadget.

@ENDNODE


@NODE FAQ
@TITLE "misterbanana  FAQ"


    @{b}Frequently Asked Question@{ub}


    Q: Why a banana?

    A: Because it's cool.


    Q: Why yellow?

    A: Because it's cool.

 
    Q: Does it make use of modern A.I. stuff?

    A. Yes. MrBanana is up-2-date A.I. science, it makes use of neuralnet.library.

    
    Q: Is it a good idea to install it to SYS:WBStartup/ ?

    A. Yes, of coz.


    Q: Why it does not use trancparency?

    A: It flickered too much, and it was not
       possible to workaround this.
    
    U: Well, now it's possible (faked, but its okay I guess)

@ENDNODE

